  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nThe ERC20 spec allows for any number of decimals. Thus, ERC20 should not enforce any opinion about it.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nConstraining decimals makes it tougher to develop with OZ's ERC20. One way in which having a default is painful is setting up mock contracts for tokens you'll interact with. If you have to work with a token with non-18 decimals, you can't use ERC20.",
